{
  "text": "Note that Hypothesis 1 is consistent with a diminished effectiveness of IPR-based technology transfer after the 2002 reform. One reason is that it may have encouraged patent applications on marginal inventions. We also expect the reform to have influenced assignment patterns, which may also have had adverse effects on technology transfer. The reform clearly favored university-assigned patents, which accordingly are predicted to have become relatively more frequent after the professors' privilege was abolished. This is consistent with the findings of [CITATION_1] for a single Japanese university.",
